Package grafioschtrader.gtnet

Enum Class GTNetMessageCodeType

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Enum<GTNetMessageCodeType>
grafioschtrader.gtnet.GTNetMessageCodeType
All Implemented Interfaces:
GTNetMessageCode, Serializable, Comparable<GTNetMessageCodeType>, Constable
public enum GTNetMessageCodeType extends Enum<GTNetMessageCodeType> implements GTNetMessageCode
Application-specific message codes for Grafioschtrader GTNet communication. This enum contains only Grafioschtrader-specific message codes (60+) for trading-related functionality like price exchange, history quotes, and security lookup. Core protocol messages (0-54) are defined in GNetCoreMessageCode in the grafiosch-base module.

Naming Convention

Message codes follow a structured naming pattern that indicates their purpose and behavior:
  • Contains _RR_: Message expects a response (Requires Response)
  • Suffix _C: Client-initiated messages (triggered from UI or scheduled jobs)
  • Suffix _S: Server response messages (replies to requests)
  • Contains _SEL_: Targeted at a specific selected remote server
  • Contains _ALL_: Broadcast to all applicable remote servers

Message Code Ranges

  1. 0-54: Core protocol messages - defined in GNetCoreMessageCode
  2. 60-64: Lastprice/intraday price exchange
  3. 70-79: Exchange configuration synchronization
  4. 80-84: Historical price exchange
  5. 90-95: Security metadata lookup (including batch)
See Also:
  • for core protocol messages (0-54)
  • for mapping message codes to payload model classes
  • for message storage and threading
